{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7a3749f4-0287-48d5-93f4-20149eaf8cf0","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is only for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so let me give you direct guidance instead.\n\n**Tools for analyzing .NET crash dumps:**\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform, recommended):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   ```\n   Useful commands inside the REPL:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack\n   - `pe` — print last exception\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n   - `threads` — list all threads\n\n2. **`lldb` with SOS** (Linux/macOS):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet-sos install\n   lldb --core your-file.dmp\n   ```\n\n3. **WinDbg** (Windows) — load SOS via `.loadby sos coreclr`\n\n**Quick triage steps:**\n1. Run `dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp`\n2. Use `pe` to print the exception that caused the crash\n3. Use `clrstack` to see the stack trace\n4. Use `threads` to check for deadlocks or problematic threads\n\nWould you like me to help you run any of these commands on your dump file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c140affb-df21-4482-ae5d-43182955d86b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\" So that skill is not appropriate here.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their crash dump.","outputTokens":434,"requestId":"2050:328887:80E3E8:9459E8:69F01399"},"id":"a0eb4715-d3ae-4e7c-a6dc-b03a8ae7f3e0","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:55:47.868Z","parentId":"1adc6e93-13de-4f53-b8da-7d152d0d5f12"}
